  tldr = {We present a perfectly-secure 4 party protocol in the partially synchronous setting with 2 initial synchronous rounds. The protocol has optimal resilience and optimal number of synchronous rounds and it partially answers one of the open problems of Patra and Ravi (IEEE Transactions on Information Theory, 2018). We also discuss concretely efficient 4 party cryptographically-secure protocols in the partially synchronous setting with 1 initial synchronous round and the completely asynchronous setting.},
